mbai","full_time_employees":188,"trailing_pe":19.927536,"price_to_book":1.8675404,"book_value":58.901,"eps_trailing":5.52,"dividend_rate":0.1,"dividend_yield":0.09,"payout_ratio":0.018099999,"five_yr_avg_div_yield":0.37,"revenue":5600811008.0,"revenue_per_share":87.248,"revenue_growth":0.103,"ebitda":794172032.0,"ebitda_margins":0.1418,"gross_margins":0.28999,"operating_margins":0.13637,"profit_margins":0.06381,"net_income":357380000.0,"total_cash":1006230976.0,"total_cash_per_share":14.994,"total_debt":2479895040.0,"debt_to_equity":62.765,"enterprise_value":8855732224.0,"enterprise_to_ebitda":11.151,"enterprise_to_revenue":1.581,"earnings_growth":0.761,"shares_outstanding":67059000.0,"float_shares":15856682.0,"held_pct_insiders":0.69891,"held_pct_institutions":0.0,"beta":-0.212,"fifty_two_week_high":205.5,"fifty_two_week_low":108.55,"fifty_day_average":137.357,"two_hundred_day_avg":153.83376,"recommendation":"none","all_time_high":445.0,"all_time_low":0.144,"long_business_summary":"Oriental Rail Infrastructure Limited manufactures, buys, and sells various recron, seat and berth, and compreg board products in India. The company offers compreg wood sheets used in electrical insulation which include rings, blocks, segments, etc.; silicon foam blocks and shuttering plates used in the manufacturing of seats and berths of railway coaches; acosonic boards used for architectural, thermal, noise barriers solutions, and turnkey projects; lavatory doors; and phenolic resins and hardners for plywood and moulded goods industries; as well as densified thermal bonded blocks. It also provides artificial leather/rexine products under ORVIN brand name used in shoes, automotive seating, commercial and residential upholstery, stationery, luggage and bags, and industrial and consumer applications. In addition, the company trades in timber woods, ferrous and non ferrous metals, casting tools, slabs, rods, section flates, and other ferrous and non-ferrous products; and manufactures heavy engineering equipment, including wagons, bogies, couplers, and draft gears. Further, it exports its products. It serves railways and other industries. The company was formerly known as Oriental Veneer Products Limited and changed its name to Oriental Rail Infrastructure Limited in March 2022. Oriental Rail Infrastructure Limited was incorporated in 1991 and is based in Mumbai, India."}}